> What part of SPARQ target is different between Apache Jena and Topquadrant SHACL?

Hi, 

The shacl-rules-graph and the data-graph are identical for both approaches, the difference only in behavior.
Here is the concrete difference:
```java
    private static Model runJenaShaclRules(Model dataModel, Model rules) {
        ValidationReport res = ShaclValidator.get().validate(rules.getGraph(), dataModel.getGraph());
        return res.getModel();
    }

    private static Model runTopbraidShaclRules(Model dataModel, Model shapesModel) {
        Resource report = org.topbraid.shacl.validation.ValidationUtil.validateModel(dataModel, shapesModel, false);
        return report.getModel();
    }
```
Another way to reproduce: download and run `simple-shack-for-test.ttl`. It contains all rules and data. For Topquadrant SHACL implementation, Topbraid Composer can be used.

